    {
      "type": "Requested Content",
      "text": "General \nEmissions must be reported in gross, not net figures. Therefore, negative numbers are not allowed.\nEntering zero suggests that you have measured your emissions and that they are equal to zero.\nYou should enter data for all Scope 3 categories for which emissions have been calculated for the reporting period specified in column 1. If you have not calculated emissions for a Scope 3 category for that reporting period, leave the corresponding column blank.\nEnsure that the reporting period represents only one full year that has already passed. Reporting periods should not be in the future. This information is important for others to understand the time dimension of your disclosure.\nEmissions estimates are acceptable, as long as there is transparency with regard to the estimation approach (what is estimated and how) and the data used for the analysis is adequate to support the objectives of the inventory. If applicable to your organization's reporting of Scope 3 emissions, please outline this in the comment column.\nEnd date (column 1) \nThe start date of each past year will be automatically assumed to be exactly 365 days before the listed date. For example, if you enter an end date of 31/12/2023, your start date will be automatically assumed to be 01/01/2023.\nNote for first time responders \nIf you are a first-time responder, please provide gross global Scope 3 emissions data for up to five years prior to the current reporting year.\nThe number of past year rows that will appear is dependent on your selection in column 6 of 1.4.\nInput Scope 3 emissions data for the year prior to the current reporting year in the first row and work backwards.\nUse the comment column to report relevant information regarding your organization's past Scope 3 emissions data, such as the emissions calculation methodologies used, and an indication of the proportion of emissions calculated using data obtained from suppliers or value chain partners.\nNote for restatements \nIf you have chosen to restate your organization's gross global Scope 3 emissions data previously supplied to CDP (as indicated in column 6 of 1.4), you may do so here. The number of past year rows that will appear is dependent on your selection in column 6 of 1.4.\nReporting recalculated figures for these years is optional.\nRestated Scope 3 emissions data needs to be entered in reverse order i.e. you should work backwards from the most recent reporting year.\nUse the comment column to identify that this is restated data and the reason for the restatement.\nFor more information on restatements see the CDP technical note on restatements here. \nNote for financial services sector companies: \nColumn 16 \"Scope 3: Investments (metric tons CO2e)\" is not shown to financial services sector companies completing the full version of the questionnaire.",
      "typeKo": "요청 내용",
      "textKo": "일반 Emissions 해야 합니다 be 보고 in gross, not net figures. Therefore, negative numbers are not allowed. Entering zero suggests that you have measured your emissions 및 that they are equal to zero. You 해야 합니다 enter data for all Scope 3 categories for which emissions have been calculated 에 대한 reporting period specified in 열 1. 만약 you have not calculated emissions for a Scope 3 category for that reporting period, leave the corresponding 열 blank. Ensure that the reporting period represents only one full year that has already passed. Reporting periods 해야 합니다 not be in the future. This information is important for others to understand the time dimension of your 공시. Emissions estimates are acceptable, as long as there is transparency with regard to the estimation approach (what is estimated 및 how) 및 the data used 에 대한 analysis is adequate to support the objectives 의 inventory. 만약 해당되는 경우 to 귀사의 reporting of Scope 3 배출량, please outline this in the Scope 3: 다운스트림 운송 및 유통(metric tons CO2e) 열. 연도 (열 1) The start date of each past year will be automatically assumed to be exactly 365 days before the listed date. For example, 만약 you enter an 연도 of 31/12/2023, your start date will be automatically assumed to be 01/01/2023. Note for first time responders 만약 you are a first-time responder, please provide 전 세계 총 Scope 3 배출량 data for up to five years prior to the current 보고연도. The number of past year 행 that will appear is dependent on your 선택 in 열 6 of 1.4. Input Scope 3 배출량 data 에 대한 year prior to the current 보고연도 in the first 행 및 work backwards. Use the Scope 3: 다운스트림 운송 및 유통(metric tons CO2e) 열 to report 관련 information regarding 귀사의 past Scope 3 배출량 data, such as the emissions 계산 methodologies used, 및 an indication 의 proportion of emissions calculated using data obtained from 공급업체 또는 가치사슬 partners. Note for restatements 만약 you have chosen to restate 귀사의 전 세계 총 Scope 3 배출량 data previously supplied to CDP (as indicated in 열 6 of 1.4), you may do so here. The number of past year 행 that will appear is dependent on your 선택 in 열 6 of 1.4. Reporting recalculated figures 에 대한se years is optional. Restated Scope 3 배출량 data needs to be entered in reverse order i.e. you 해야 합니다 work backwards from the most recent 보고연도. Use the Scope 3: 다운스트림 운송 및 유통(metric tons CO2e) 열 to identify that this is restated data 및 the reason 에 대한 restatement. For more information on restatements see the CDP technical note on restatements here. Note for 금융 서비스 sector companies: 열 16 \"Scope 3: Investments (미터톤 CO2e)\" is not shown to 금융 서비스 sector companies completing the full version 의 질문서."
